BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:xlwd8fdSFgj_BUzQcMDcQ
SUMMARY:Philippe Jaroussky and Artaserse
DTSTAMP:20260413T005343Z
DTSTART:20260430T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Recognized for the pyrotechnic character of his vocal art\\\, P
	hilippe Jaroussky has also recently joined the field of orchestral conduct
	ing. With his own ensemble founded in 2002\\\, he takes on this double rol
	e of soloist and conductor and offers a bouquet of 18th century Italian ca
	ntatas on the passionate theme of jealousy. \\nThis concert is dedicated t
	o the memory of Naomi Shiff \\nAn enthusiastic and skilled early-music ama
	teur\\\, Naomi Shiff’s passion was playing Renaissance music from original
	 notation\\\, and she was a devoted supporter of Early Music Seattle\\\, t
	he Seattle Recorder Society\\\, and EMA\\\, among others. Professionally\\
	\, she was among the first female computer programmers. A family death not
	ice mentioned that\\\, “in keeping with her love of learning\\\, she had h
	er remarkable brain donated to the University of Washington Brain Study.” 
	\\n\\nEvents are offered for informational\\\, entertainment\\\, and educa
	tional purposes only. Read Town Hall’s Program Content Policy.\n\nhttps://
	townhallseattle.org/event/philippe-jaroussky-and-artaserse/\n\nFrom Town H
	all Seattle
URL:https://townhallseattle.org/event/philippe-jaroussky-and-artaserse/
LOCATION:The Great Hall\\\, 1119 Eighth Avenue (enter on Eighth Avenue)\\\,
	 Seattle\\\, 98101\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:town-hall-seattle
CATEGORIES:Town Hall Seattle
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT
